subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis:
Prozona short and high with distinct lobes; lateral projections of mesozona distinct; metazona long, slightly raised, its lateral margins straight, hind margin rounded (
Figs. 5a–d
) narrower in some specimens than that of the figures; male tegmina (
Figs. 5a, c, e
) broad and long, reaching always beyond hind knee; axillary 1 and axillary 2 veins of hind wing distinct and separated; distal excision of dorsal carina of hind femur distinct, its ventral carina clearly wavy; inner side of hind femur darkened with dark blue macula but always surrounded with red color; inner side of hind tibia dark red; male penis valves (

Figs. 
5g
, h

) stout apically (but slender than that of the following subspecies), their apices strongly curved upwards in lateral view, widened in posterior view; lophi (
Fig. 5i
) with more than 15 dense spines, posterior margin of epiphallus (
Fig. 5i
) with a rounded projection.
